一些评论家也发现了米利厄斯将《野蛮人柯南》视为一部歌剧来进行拍摄的想法，艾利和哈克维尔就看到了电影与瓦格纳歌剧间的联系<ref name="Elley" /><ref name="Huckvale" />。据哈克维尔所说，电影开场时的戏段与《[[齐格弗里德_(歌剧)|齐格弗里德]]》中锻制宝剑的场景很相似，柯南的历险和考验也似乎是受到了[[齐格弗里德|歌剧中英雄]]经历的启发：目睹父母的惨死，身为奴隶慢慢长大，杀死一条巨蛇（龙）。此外，施瓦辛格的扮相也与哈克维尔心目中的齐格弗里德类似：一个“雅利安金发野兽”的角色模型<ref name="Huckvale" />。这个雅利安英雄所象征的种族优越性概念，受到了詹姆斯·威尔科特和J·霍伯曼（{{lang|en|J. Hoberman}}）的批判。他们强调片中使用的尼采题辞，并将主角与尼采的[[超人说|超人说]]联系起来<ref name"Hoberman">{{cite book |last1=Hoberman |first1=James |editor1-last=Arroyo |editor1-first=José |title=Action/Spectacle Cinema |year=2000 |publisher=British Film Institute |location=London, United Kingdom |isbn=0-85170-756-4 |pages=29-33 |chapter=Nietzsche's Boy}}  This article was originally published in {{cite journal |journal=Sight and Sound |volume=1 |issue=5 |page=30 |location=London, United Kingdom |publisher=British Film Institute |issn=0037-4806|date=1991年9月}}</ref><ref name="Wolcott">{{cite journal |last=Wolcott |first=James |title=Movies |journal=Texas Monthly |volume=10 |issue=7 |page=160 |location=Texas, United States |publisher=Mediatex Communications |issn=0148-7736 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=7y0EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA154 |accessdate=2013-12-16|date=1982年7月}}</ref>。艾伯特对其中“北欧超人对抗黑人”的描绘感到不安，“金发肌肉男”砍下黑人的头并“轻蔑地抛下楼梯”<ref name="Ebert" />。研究[[亚瑟王|亚瑟王]]的学者亚当·罗伯茨（{{lang|en|Adam Roberts}}）也有这种感觉，他还认为本片是20世纪80年代初期有法西斯主义严重渗透的剑与魔法电影代表。据罗伯茨所说，本片沿用了[[莱尼·里芬斯塔尔|莱尼·里芬斯塔尔]]为[[纳粹德国|纳粹德国]]奠定的思想和美学。他还警告说，任何对这些剑与魔法电影有关法西斯主义的解读都是主观性的<ref>{{cite book |last1=Roberts |first1=Adam |title=Silk and Potatoes: Contemporary Arthurian Fantasy |series=Costerus New Series |volume=114 |year=1998 |publisher=Rodopi Publishers |location=Amsterdam, Netherlands |isbn=90-420-0306-5 |pages=110-111 |chapter=Arthurian Cinema: Aesthetic Fascism and Its Critique}}</ref>。不过，电影评论家理查德·戴尔（{{lang|en|Richard Dyer}}）则认为对《野蛮人柯南》的这些解读都是不准确的，是对尼采哲学的误解<ref>{{cite book |last1=Dyer |first1=Richard |editor1-last=Adams |editor1-first=Rachel |editor2-last=Savran |editor2-first=David |title=The Masculinity Studies Reader |year=2002 |publisher=Blackwell Publishers |location=Oxford, United Kingdom |isbn=0-631-22660-5 |page=265 |chapter=The White Man's Muscles}}  This was originally printed in {{cite book |title=White |year=1997 |publisher=Routledge |location=London, United Kingdom |isbn=0-415-09537-9 |pages=145-153, 155-165, 230-231}}</ref>，部分哲学学者也表示电影界经常会误解“超人”这一概念背后的含义<ref>{{cite book |last1=Jovanovski |first1=Thomas |title=Aesthetic Transformations: Taking Nietzsche at His Word |series=American University studies |volume=204 |year=2008 |publisher=Peter Lang |location=New York, United States |isbn=978-0-8204-2002-8 |page=105 |chapter=Übermensch on Parade}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Solomon |first1=Robert C. |title=The Joy of Philosophy: Thinking Thin Versus the Passionate Life |url=https://archive.org/details/joyofphilosophyt0000solo |year=2003 |origyear=1999 |publisher=Oxford University Press |location=New York, United States |isbn=0-19-506759-2 |page=[https://archive.org/details/joyofphilosophyt0000solo/page/33 33] |chapter=The Will to Power as Virtue}}</ref>。

《野蛮人柯南》也被视为时代的产物，电影的主题反映了20世纪80年代美国的政治气候。[[罗纳德·里根|罗纳德·里根]]当选[[美国总统|总统]]后的8年时间里，[[个人主义|个人主义]]理念得到了加强。他在演讲中强调个人的道德价值，鼓励他的美国同胞让国家更加成功，并且在冷战中站起来与[[苏联|苏联]]对抗<ref>{{cite book |last1=Shaw |first1=Tony |title=Hollywood's Cold War |url=https://archive.org/details/hollywoodscoldwa00shaw |year=2007 |publisher=Edinburgh University Press |location=Edinburgh, United Kingdom |isbn=978-1-55849-612-5 |pages=[https://archive.org/details/hollywoodscoldwa00shaw/page/n277 267]-269 |chapter=The Empire Strikes Back}}</ref><ref name="Saunders" />{{rp|48-49}}<!-- Hunter simply ascribed those films as having anarcho-individualism as a theme.-->。南埃塞克斯延续和高等教育学院讲师，电影评论员戴夫·桑德斯（{{lang|en|Dave Saunders}}）博士将《野蛮人柯南》与里根主义联系起来<ref name="Saunders" />{{rp|51}}，这位总统的政策周围环绕着[[保守主义|保守主义]]意识形态<ref name="Kellner">{{cite book |last1=Kellner |first1=Douglas |editor-last=Schatz |editor-first=Thomas |title=Hollywood: Cultural Dimensions: Ideology, Identity and Cultural Industry Studies |series=Hollywood: Critical Concepts in Media and Cultural Studies |volume=4 |year=2004 |publisher=Routledge |location=London, United Kingdom |isbn=0-415-28131-8 |pages=73 |chapter=Films, Politics, and Ideology: Reflections on Hollywood Film in the Age of Reagan}}</ref>。他还将柯南和杜姆的对抗比喻为美国人的圣战<ref name="Saunders" />{{rp|51}}，他选择的武器是原始的剑，而里根是用精神来与苏联对抗<ref name="Saunders" />{{rp|51-52}}，杜姆的老巢则与[[莫斯科|莫斯科]]的[[克里姆林宫|克里姆林宫]]对比<ref name="Saunders" />{{rp|57}}。在桑德斯看来，柯南是美国式英雄的象征，他从考验与磨难中汲取力量，并且用美国人的方式击败并杀死邪恶的压迫者（苏联）<ref name="Saunders" />{{rp|53-58}}。凯尔纳和他的学者同事迈克尔·瑞恩（{{lang|en|Michael Ryan}}）则提出美国个人主义的另一个敌人：一个过分扩张盛气凌人的联邦政府<ref name="RyanKellner">{{cite book |last1=Ryan |first1=Michael |last2=Kellner |first2=Douglas |title=Camera Politica: The Politics and Ideology of Contemporary Hollywood Film |edition=First Midland Book |year=1990 |origyear=1988 |publisher=Indiana University Press |location=Indiana, United States |isbn=0-253-20604-9 |pages=219-228 |chapter=The Triumph of Individualism—From Man to Superman |chapterurl=http://books.google.com/books?id=S9KZQ3iHeE0C&pg=PA219}}</ref>{{rp|226}}。对电影存在的个人主义联想并不局限于美国，文化历史学家杰弗瑞·理查兹（{{lang|en|Jeffrey Richards}}）注意到了电影在英国青少年中的知名度<ref name="Richards1997">{{cite book |last1=Richards |first1=Jeffrey |title=Films and British National Identity: From Dickens to Dad's Army |series=Studies in Popular Culture |year=1997 |publisher=Manchester University Press |location=Manchester, United Kingdom |isbn=0-7190-4743-9}}</ref>{{rp|23, 170}}，电影评论家罗宾·伍德（{{lang|en|Robin Wood}}）表示，在大多数情况下，个人主义和法西斯主义的区别是很小的，他还认为《野蛮人柯南》是那个时代唯一一部直接抛开了伪装，公开为法西斯主义理想庆祝的电影<ref name="Wood">{{cite book |last1=Wood |first1=Robin |title=Hollywood from Vietnam to Reagan ... and Beyond |url=https://archive.org/details/hollywoodfromvie00wood_341 |edition=Revised and expanded |year=2003 |origyear=1986 |publisher=Columbia University Press |location=New York, United States |isbn=0-231-12967-X |pages=[https://archive.org/details/hollywoodfromvie00wood_341/page/n192 144]-167 |chapter=Papering the Cracks: Fantasy and Ideology in the Reagan Era}}</ref>{{rp|152}}。

